 and describes how the necessarily imperfect connection between science and truth leads to researchers' values influencing their findings. The resulting book is a tour de force, a synthesis of the study of idealization that also offers countless new insights and avenues for future exploration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aIdealism. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 4acausation. 4aexplanation. 4aidealization. 4alevels of organization. 4apluralism. 4ascientific aims. 4aunderstanding. 4avalues in science. 70(DE-601)1049329530(DE-588)4231385-5aIdealisierung2gnd 70(DE-601)1062193240(DE-588)4041421-8aNaturwissenschaften2gnd 70(DE-601)1062717090(DE-588)4030102-3aKausalität2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226507194423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226507194.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles